# **8. Circular Next Greater Element**

For circular arrays, index wraps around.

### **Implementation**

```cpp
vector<int> nextGreaterCircular(vector<int> &a) {
    int n = a.size();
    vector<int> ans(n, -1);
    stack<int> st;

    for (int i = 2*n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        int idx = i % n;

        while (!st.empty() && st.top() <= a[idx])
            st.pop();

        if (i < n && !st.empty())
            ans[idx] = st.top();

        st.push(a[idx]);
    }
    return ans;
}
```

